00:07.240 --> 00:09.608
- Previously on <i>the affair...</i>

00:09.610 --> 00:12.478
- Mr. Solloway,
thanks for coming in.

00:12.480 --> 00:14.346
- Well,
like I had much of a choice.

00:14.348 --> 00:15.647
- Where's martin?

00:15.649 --> 00:18.283
- I hate grandpa.
- I know. So do I.

00:18.285 --> 00:21.387
At least you stand to inherit
some of his money when he dies.

00:21.389 --> 00:22.654
- So I read your book.

00:22.656 --> 00:25.224
Everyone has one book in them.

00:25.226 --> 00:27.092
Almost nobody has two.

00:27.094 --> 00:29.261
- Why're you laughing?
- It's--

00:29.263 --> 00:31.497
- What? Why you laughing?
- Your face is a little funny.

00:31.499 --> 00:33.432
That's all.
[giggles]

00:33.434 --> 00:35.100
- Welcome to the end
of the world.

00:35.102 --> 00:37.369
- Do you remember the first time
you saw her?

00:37.371 --> 00:39.104
- Like it was yesterday.

00:39.106 --> 00:41.373
- Ms. Lockhart, do you remember
seeing him for the first time?

00:41.375 --> 00:44.076
- Turn her over.
- Hit her hard!

00:44.078 --> 00:45.577
- I remember he
was holding his daughter.

00:45.579 --> 00:47.112
[overlapping shouting]

00:47.114 --> 00:49.782
- You saved her life.
I'm noah, by the way.

00:49.784 --> 00:52.117
- Why don't you tell me
how it began?

00:52.119 --> 00:55.087
- How many times do you think
we've had sex?

00:55.089 --> 00:56.488
10,000?

00:56.490 --> 00:57.790
- Yeah, maybe.

00:57.792 --> 01:01.326
Let's try to have
a good day today.

01:01.328 --> 01:04.663
I wake up every morning
with his face in my mind too.

01:04.665 --> 01:07.566
- It just hurts.
Make it stop.

01:08.701 --> 01:11.270
- Alison?
- You found me!

01:11.272 --> 01:13.405
- I found you.
- Oh, hi.

01:13.407 --> 01:15.207
- You live around here?

01:15.209 --> 01:17.209
- Walk me home then?

01:17.211 --> 01:19.144
I think you want to see this.

01:19.146 --> 01:23.715
- I got to go.
- Thanks for the walk.

01:23.717 --> 01:25.784
Oh, no.

01:25.786 --> 01:27.553
So go.

01:27.555 --> 01:30.489
- Leave me alone!
- Stop it!

01:34.494 --> 01:36.428
- How much longer
is this gonna take?

01:36.430 --> 01:38.597
- I just have
a few more questions.

01:47.407 --> 01:50.442
- ♪ I was screaming
into the canyon ♪

01:50.444 --> 01:53.712
♪ at the moment
of my death ♪

01:53.714 --> 01:57.216
♪ the echo I created

01:57.218 --> 01:59.885
♪ outlasted my last breath

01:59.887 --> 02:03.489
♪ my voice,
