03:02.182 --> 03:06.652
- Listen, I had no idea she was
married when I first met her.

03:06.654 --> 03:10.622
I mean, how would I have known?
She never mentioned it.

03:10.624 --> 03:14.927
She seemed like
the loneliest girl in the world.

03:24.871 --> 03:27.873
I just thought she was bad news.

03:32.445 --> 03:37.950
So, after that first night I
went out of my way to avoid her.

03:48.428 --> 03:50.562
I had my second book on my mind.

03:50.564 --> 03:53.932
I was under a lot of pressure
to get it done, make it good.

03:53.934 --> 03:59.438
[boat horns honking,
gulls crying]

03:59.440 --> 04:03.342
[background chatter]

04:07.880 --> 04:10.349
- I just picked up a copy
of that book.

04:10.351 --> 04:12.551
I'm looking forward
to reading it.

04:12.553 --> 04:15.587
- Oh, good for you, man.

04:15.589 --> 04:18.423
I hope you enjoy it.

04:18.425 --> 04:22.728
Anyway, the point is I wasn't
thinking about her at all.

04:44.450 --> 04:47.286
[groaning]

04:47.288 --> 04:49.488
Oh, go--

05:00.366 --> 05:05.504
[no audible dialogue]
[shower running]

05:05.506 --> 05:07.639
[door opens]

05:07.641 --> 05:08.640
- Hi.

05:08.642 --> 05:09.975
- Hi.

05:11.911 --> 05:14.413
- Want some company?

05:14.415 --> 05:16.581
- Uh...

05:16.583 --> 05:18.784
Not really.

05:18.786 --> 05:21.653
- Gee, thanks.

05:21.655 --> 05:24.990
- I'm taking some me time.

05:24.992 --> 05:29.561
- You know, you're not as much
fun as you used to be.

05:29.563 --> 05:32.931
- I was never fun.
I think you've become more fun.

05:32.933 --> 05:34.966
I think that's the problem.

05:37.537 --> 05:42.107
- I'm gonna go find a pool boy
that lets me shower with him.

05:42.109 --> 05:46.812
- Can we have breakfast
together before you do?

05:55.121 --> 05:58.857
- Ready?
Whoops, that's a big one.

05:58.859 --> 06:02.394
[sizzling sound]
go for it.

06:02.396 --> 06:04.730
They're in the cabinet
next to the fridge.

06:04.732 --> 06:06.798
Advil, right?

06:06.800 --> 06:09.468
- I could have sworn they
were there last summer.

06:09.470 --> 06:10.836
- They were.

06:10.838 --> 06:13.372
Mother had an efficiency
expert re-do the kitchen.

06:13.374 --> 06:14.973
- That's right,
and she was worth every penny.

06:14.975 --> 06:16.975
I got years
of my life back.

06:16.977 --> 06:18.677
- Coffee!
- Miranda,

06:18.679 --> 06:21.113
Make sure the caterers know
we increased the guest count

06:21.115 --> 06:23.048
To 200 people.

06:23.050 --> 06:25.550
- Good morning, mr. Solloway.

06:25.552 --> 06:27.119
- Hello, ruby.
- Checkmate!

06:27.121 --> 06:29.721
- No, it isn't.
- Yes, it is.

06:29.723 --> 06:32.791
- Trevor, it's highly unlikely
you're gonna win this game.

06:32.793 --> 06:33.959
I'm older and I'm smarter--

06:33.961 --> 06:35.594
- Well,
you could let him win, dad.

06:35.596 --> 06:37.729
- Why would I do that?
- Because he's ten.

06:37.731 --> 06:39.698
- So we're gonna let him think
he's better than he is?

06:39.700 --> 06:40.932
How will real life feel?

06:40.934 --> 06:42.701
- He'll be an adult
in real life,

06:42.703 --> 06:44.469
So it will feel fine.
- Checkmate.

06:44.471 --> 06:46.004
- Daddy, please make me
a cappuccino.

06:46.006 --> 06:47.839
- I would, whit, if I
could work out how to use this--

06:47.841 --> 06:49.708
- Don't touch that!

06:49.710 --> 06:51.743
It's a very temperamental
machine.

06:51.745 --> 06:53.545
We've had such headaches

06:53.547 --> 06:55.113
With well-intentioned visitors

06:55.115 --> 06:56.782
Inadvertently reprogramming it.

06:56.784 --> 06:58.517
Miranda, would you please--

06:58.519 --> 07:00.185
- Cappuccino or espresso?

07:00.187 --> 07:02.020
- Macchiato, please.
Thank you.

07:02.022 --> 07:04.189
- Oh, my god!
Miranda, the flowers!

07:04.191 --> 07:08.093
We completely, utterly, entirely
forgot to order flowers.

07:08.095 --> 07:09.861
- Oh, no.
- What are we gonna do?

07:09.863 --> 07:11.963
- Calm down. Just relax.
It's okay.

07:11.965 --> 07:14.599
Noah and I will go
to the farmer's market today.

07:14.601 --> 07:16.701
I'll get you some flowers,
and I'll arrange them for you.

07:16.703 --> 07:19.738
- Noah shouldn't have
to spend his Saturday like that.

07:19.740 --> 07:20.839
- He doesn't mind.

07:20.841 --> 07:22.474
Do you?

07:22.476 --> 07:23.775
- Not at all.

07:23.777 --> 07:25.877
- [laughs]
great!

07:29.048 --> 07:31.082
- How come ruby's hanging out
with us again?

07:31.084 --> 07:33.084
I thought you guys
said she was a bad influence.

07:33.086 --> 07:34.753
- 'cause she's a friend
of your sister's,

07:34.755 --> 07:36.788
And I think that she's
grown up a lot this year.

07:36.790 --> 07:37.989
- I heard she got expelled.

07:37.991 --> 07:39.991
- Is that true?
- No.

07:39.993 --> 07:43.495
She spent a little time
in rehab.

07:43.497 --> 07:44.863
- Horsies! Stop!

07:44.865 --> 07:45.931
I want to pet the horsie!

07:45.933 --> 07:47.933
- Uh, we can't stop now, honey,

07:47.935 --> 07:49.601
But on the way back we can.

07:49.603 --> 07:50.836
- But I want to pet the horsie!

07:50.838 --> 07:53.605
- You will. I promise.
On the way back.

07:53.607 --> 07:57.008
I used to ride there
when I was a little girl.

07:57.010 --> 08:00.145
- Do you know how many times
you've told me that?

08:00.147 --> 08:04.182
- Well, you repeat things too,
you know.

08:05.685 --> 08:08.487
There's a really nice woman
that ran that ranch.

08:08.489 --> 08:10.088
She had four boys.

08:10.090 --> 08:12.257
They must be all grown up
by now.

08:12.259 --> 08:14.059
- Mm. I knew that.

08:14.061 --> 08:16.828
[pop music on radio]

08:16.830 --> 08:18.263
[chuckles]

08:19.966 --> 08:24.102
- I spy with my little eye
something white.

08:24.104 --> 08:25.704
- Something white?

08:25.706 --> 08:27.172
Her dress.

08:27.174 --> 08:29.808
- Yes.
- [chuckles]

08:29.810 --> 08:33.979
I spy with my little eyes--

08:37.850 --> 08:40.719
- What? What do you see?

08:45.858 --> 08:47.659
- Disaster.

08:55.034 --> 08:57.235
- Hello.
- Hi.

08:57.237 --> 08:59.571
- Would you like
to try a sample?

08:59.573 --> 09:02.007
- Yes.
- Okay.

09:02.009 --> 09:04.809
This one is strawberry-peach.

09:04.811 --> 09:07.279
How do you like it?
Better than the blueberry?

09:07.281 --> 09:09.080
- Hm.

09:09.082 --> 09:11.583
- And this one...
- How are you?

09:12.618 --> 09:14.152
- I'm fine.

09:15.955 --> 09:17.589
- How do you like it?
- Mm-hmm.

09:17.591 --> 09:21.126
- I've been, uh...
A bit worried about you, uh--

09:21.128 --> 09:23.595
- Do you two know each other?

09:23.597 --> 09:25.096
- Not really.

09:26.899 --> 09:29.200
- Apples?
- Yes, it has apples in it,

09:29.202 --> 09:31.069
But there's also
a secret ingredient.

09:31.071 --> 09:33.004
- Cinnamon?
- Yes.

09:33.006 --> 09:34.306
What a smart girl you are.

09:34.308 --> 09:35.607
So you want one?

09:35.609 --> 09:36.942
- Daddy, can we have it?

09:36.944 --> 09:39.044
- Sure, honey. Yeah.

09:39.046 --> 09:40.979
- It's 12 bucks, please.

09:42.214 --> 09:45.984
- I've only got a 20, so,
uh, keep the change.

09:45.986 --> 09:48.153
- No, thanks.

09:49.922 --> 09:51.323
- Hey. Here you are.
- Mama!

09:51.325 --> 09:52.357
- Hey!

09:52.359 --> 09:55.994
[helen and stacey
chattering]

10:00.766 --> 10:03.134
- Everything okay?

10:03.136 --> 10:05.604
- Yeah. Everything's fine.

10:05.606 --> 10:07.172
- Horsies! Horsies!

10:07.174 --> 10:08.940
- [laughs]
uh, I promised--

10:08.942 --> 10:11.009
- All right.

10:18.751 --> 10:22.654
[bell ringing]

10:24.190 --> 10:25.957
[ding]
- all right.

10:25.959 --> 10:28.159
I think they heard it.
Nice work.

10:29.629 --> 10:30.729
- Howdy.

10:30.731 --> 10:31.997
- Hi, I'm helen butler.

10:31.999 --> 10:34.733
I used to ride here
when I was a kid.

10:36.302 --> 10:39.137
But you were very young,
so you probably don't remember.

10:39.139 --> 10:40.372
- [chuckling]
isn't that something?

10:40.374 --> 10:42.107
It's good to see you again,
helen.

10:42.109 --> 10:43.708
Is this your daughter?
- Yes.

10:43.710 --> 10:46.111
We would like to sign her up
for some lessons.

10:46.113 --> 10:47.846
- I'm sure that can be arranged.

10:47.848 --> 10:49.714
Hey!

10:49.716 --> 10:51.316
This is my brother, hal.

10:51.318 --> 10:53.418
He can help you
pick out a horse.

10:53.420 --> 10:56.121
What's your name?
- Stacey.

10:56.123 --> 10:57.756
- Come with me, stacey.

10:57.758 --> 11:01.126
- In the meantime,
I'll give the rest of you folks

11:01.128 --> 11:03.395
A tour of the place?
- Great.

11:03.397 --> 11:05.163
- Now, when she gets
good enough,

11:05.165 --> 11:07.265
We'll take her riding
on that trail up there,

11:07.267 --> 11:09.968
Up over the ridge
and all the way down to the sea.

11:09.970 --> 11:11.069
- Are--are you cole?

11:11.071 --> 11:12.904
- Uh, no, I'm scotty.

11:12.906 --> 11:15.273
Cole's another brother.
- Oh.

11:15.275 --> 11:16.374
- Are you looking for him?

11:16.376 --> 11:20.145
'cause there he is, right there.

11:20.147 --> 11:22.414
Hey, cole!
- Hey.

11:24.083 --> 11:25.884
Hey, folks.
Whoa.

11:27.920 --> 11:30.722
- Hey, uh, this young fellow
had a question for you.

11:30.724 --> 11:33.925
- Uh, I was wondering if you,
uh, you still need a hand?

11:33.927 --> 11:37.462
- Well, you're a little younger
than I was expecting.

11:37.464 --> 11:40.398
You ever ridden a horse before?
- No.

11:40.400 --> 11:42.767
- You ever worked on a ranch?

11:42.769 --> 11:44.469
- No.
- A farm?

11:44.471 --> 11:48.339
- I, uh, water my dad's planter
boxes every other day.

11:51.444 --> 11:53.344
- Um, I'm noah.

11:53.346 --> 11:55.914
- Cole.
- This is helen.

11:55.916 --> 11:57.115
- Ma'am.

11:57.117 --> 11:59.718
Well, you're not qualified,

11:59.720 --> 12:01.186
But you are first,

12:01.188 --> 12:02.353
And that does count
for something.

12:02.355 --> 12:04.122
So I'll tell you what.

12:04.124 --> 12:06.424
Why don't you spend a couple
more hours here with us today,

12:06.426 --> 12:08.126
If it's all right
with your folks.

12:08.128 --> 12:10.061
I'll teach you how to brush
a horse, polish a saddle.

12:10.063 --> 12:11.496
See if you got the stuff.
- Can I?

12:11.498 --> 12:13.765
- Yeah, sure.
- No, I don't know, I don't--

12:13.767 --> 12:14.799
- Yeah. Sure.

12:14.801 --> 12:16.234
- What about your parents'
party?

12:16.236 --> 12:17.769
- We'll just pick him up
later.

12:17.771 --> 12:19.804
He's excited.
It's like a miracle.

12:19.806 --> 12:20.905
Please?

12:23.309 --> 12:26.478
- Yeah. Great. Thanks.
- It's my pleasure, sir.

12:26.480 --> 12:27.946
I like your boy.

12:27.948 --> 12:30.181
All right.
First lesson.

12:30.183 --> 12:32.984
Take those into the barn.

12:37.356 --> 12:39.758
- You folks want to head up?

12:44.964 --> 12:47.966
- Everyone says to you when
you're young, "who do you love?

12:47.968 --> 12:52.303
Love is all you need,"
and it sends you into a panic.

12:52.305 --> 12:55.039
At least it did for me.

12:55.041 --> 12:56.374
My mother had just died,

12:56.376 --> 12:59.377
And my father
was drinking himself to death.

12:59.379 --> 13:02.380
My sister had taken off
for nepal with some sherpa,

13:02.382 --> 13:06.785
And I thought, "who do I love?
Who do I even have?"

13:08.120 --> 13:10.121
I had helen.

13:10.123 --> 13:13.992
I popped the question the night
we graduated college.

13:13.994 --> 13:15.527
None of my family had come,

13:15.529 --> 13:17.095
But helen's parents
took us both out

13:17.097 --> 13:18.863
To the nicest restaurant
in town,

13:18.865 --> 13:23.501
And her dad
bought a $200 bottle of wine...

13:23.503 --> 13:26.371
And afterwards all our friends
were so excited.

13:26.373 --> 13:29.240
She felt like
some sort of princess,

13:29.242 --> 13:32.177
And I felt like...Such a man.

13:32.179 --> 13:34.979
[chuckles]

13:34.981 --> 13:36.915
- Why are you laughing?

13:36.917 --> 13:38.283
- Oh, nothing.

13:38.285 --> 13:40.251
Just for some reason
that strikes me as funny,

13:40.253 --> 13:43.221
Thinking about that now.

13:49.228 --> 13:52.931
- I made you some lunch.

13:52.933 --> 13:56.067
- Oh, thanks.
- How's it going?

13:56.069 --> 14:00.338
- Badly.
- Oh. What's wrong?

14:00.340 --> 14:03.308
- Uh, I'm not inspired,
helen, I'm...

14:03.310 --> 14:05.276
I'm bored.
- Oh...

14:05.278 --> 14:06.611
I'm sorry.

14:06.613 --> 14:09.280
I'll try not to
take that personally.

14:21.393 --> 14:23.928
- This is delicious.
What is it?

14:23.930 --> 14:29.601
And some of that jam
you got at the farmer's market.

14:29.603 --> 14:31.569
Which dress?

14:31.571 --> 14:34.405
- Um...That one.

14:35.908 --> 14:38.443
- I think I'm gonna wear
this one.

14:46.051 --> 14:49.287
[overlapping chatter]

14:55.094 --> 14:56.327
- Whitney?
- Hey.

14:56.329 --> 14:58.162
- Whitney!
- What?

14:58.164 --> 15:00.365
- Come here.

15:00.367 --> 15:03.101
Where is the rest of
your dress?

15:03.103 --> 15:04.602
- Dad.

15:04.604 --> 15:05.904
- Go change.

15:05.906 --> 15:07.572
- I don't have
anything else to wear.

15:07.574 --> 15:09.507
- Then stay in your room.

15:09.509 --> 15:11.910
- Thanks a lot, dad.

15:13.479 --> 15:16.915
- Ruby, you can't drink.
You're 16.

15:20.386 --> 15:22.453
- It's apple juice.

15:27.693 --> 15:30.261
- Something totally fucked up
is happening.

15:30.263 --> 15:33.531
- What?
What is it?

15:33.533 --> 15:37.135
- Something totally fucked up is
going on, that's what.

15:40.506 --> 15:42.573
All right. See that lady
with the witchy hair

15:42.575 --> 15:44.409
And the long dre--don't look!

15:44.411 --> 15:45.476
- Well,
how am I supposed to see--

15:45.478 --> 15:47.145
- That's her.
- Who?

15:47.147 --> 15:48.680
- The piano teacher.

15:48.682 --> 15:51.215
- Who? The one your dad
had the affair with?

15:51.217 --> 15:52.684
- Yeah.

15:52.686 --> 15:54.519
- What was the name, maria?
- Theresa.

15:54.521 --> 15:56.421
- Theresa. I knew it was
something catholic.

15:56.423 --> 15:58.022
- What is she doing here?

15:58.024 --> 16:00.024
Do you think he invited her?
- Why would he do that?

16:00.026 --> 16:02.694
- 'cause he's a dick,
or hadn't you noticed?

16:02.696 --> 16:04.462
- Yeah.
- That's a rhetorical question.

16:04.464 --> 16:06.664
Don't answer it.

16:06.666 --> 16:09.701
What am I gonna do?
I don't want my mom to see her.

16:09.703 --> 16:11.402
- Did your mom know?
- Yeah, she knew.

16:11.404 --> 16:13.304
I mean, she didn't know,
but she knew.

16:13.306 --> 16:15.440
It--she knew.

16:15.442 --> 16:17.008
It's--oh, fuck.

16:17.010 --> 16:19.177
I can't believe she came.
It's so unfair.

16:19.179 --> 16:20.511
My mother worked
so fucking hard

16:20.513 --> 16:22.246
To make everything perfect
