36:38.564 --> 36:41.464
You have to come home and get
cleaned up for the party.

36:41.466 --> 36:44.467
- [sighs]
is it okay if I leave?

36:44.469 --> 36:46.303
- Yeah. Of course it is, man.

36:46.305 --> 36:47.637
That was an excellent first day.

36:47.639 --> 36:50.407
We're happy to have you here.

36:51.709 --> 36:53.543
- So what is it you boys
do here?

36:53.545 --> 36:55.245
- Whitney--
- well, miss, we, uh--

36:55.247 --> 36:56.813
We board horses,
lead trail rides--

36:56.815 --> 36:58.848
- I've never been on a horse.
- Never?

36:58.850 --> 37:02.319
- No. Something tells me
I'd love it

37:03.721 --> 37:05.555
- Whitney, come on!
Let's go!

37:05.557 --> 37:07.958
- I'm a dancer,
so I've got really loose hips.

37:07.960 --> 37:10.961
- Well, it'd be my pleasure
to teach you how to ride.

37:10.963 --> 37:12.696
[car door opens]

37:12.698 --> 37:14.764
[car door closes]

37:17.435 --> 37:19.736
- Dude, what the fuck?

37:19.738 --> 37:21.972
- She's 16. If that.

37:21.974 --> 37:24.474
- I'm just trying
to drum up some business for us.

37:24.476 --> 37:26.643
We're a little strapped
for cash these days,

37:26.645 --> 37:28.245
In case you hadn't noticed.

37:28.247 --> 37:30.780
[car motor receding]

37:36.754 --> 37:38.788
- How was the pick-up
this morning?

37:38.790 --> 37:41.558
- Oh, it was fine.

37:41.560 --> 37:44.427
- No incidents?
- No.

38:01.279 --> 38:02.612
Oh.
[laughs]

38:02.614 --> 38:04.748
- Sorry, love.
I didn't mean to frighten you.

38:04.750 --> 38:06.416
- No. That's all right.

38:06.418 --> 38:08.818
- I'm just glad to have
caught you alone for a minute.

38:08.820 --> 38:12.422
I've been hoping for some time
with you.

38:12.424 --> 38:14.057
- Okay.

38:16.494 --> 38:17.794
- How are you?

38:17.796 --> 38:20.897
- I'm fine.

38:20.899 --> 38:23.566
- Is cole being good to you?
- Mm-hmm.

38:23.568 --> 38:25.869
Yeah. Always, cherry.

38:25.871 --> 38:27.504
- I'm so proud of the way

38:27.506 --> 38:30.707
You two have gotten
through this together.

38:30.709 --> 38:34.044
Such a testament to your love.

38:34.046 --> 38:36.913
I always knew you two
were right for each other.

38:36.915 --> 38:39.983
Even when you were little
and you hated each other.

38:44.555 --> 38:47.524
I've wanted to tell you, dear,

38:47.526 --> 38:51.895
Your strength
allows us all to be strong.

38:51.897 --> 38:53.330
There have been so many nights

38:53.332 --> 38:55.532
Where I've woken up
just sobbing.

38:55.534 --> 38:59.669
Then I think of you...

38:59.671 --> 39:01.805
And of cole,

39:01.807 --> 39:04.074
And I think of
how blessed I am

39:04.076 --> 39:07.944
To have
such remarkable children.

39:07.946 --> 39:09.646
I'm sorry.
- No, no.

39:09.648 --> 39:12.615
- This is not how I intended
this conversation to go.

39:12.617 --> 39:14.351
- Don't cry. Please.

39:16.420 --> 39:18.555
It's okay.
- I was thinking,

39:18.557 --> 39:21.091
This fall, I'm gonna finally go
through the boys' old rooms.

39:21.093 --> 39:23.026
I'm gonna clear 'em out.

39:23.028 --> 39:24.694
I'm gonna have a huge tag sale.

39:24.696 --> 39:26.696
What do you think of that?
- I think you'll be rich.

39:26.698 --> 39:27.964
There's so much up there.

39:27.966 --> 39:31.835
- I know,
and then there will be room

39:31.837 --> 39:34.104
If you and cole
have another baby,

39:34.106 --> 39:38.141
And you decide to move
back in for a while.

39:38.143 --> 39:42.712
- What, move back here?
- Only if you want to, dear.

39:42.714 --> 39:44.047
I just thought it might be nice

39:44.049 --> 39:46.983
For you to have some help
next time around.

40:04.101 --> 40:08.138
- I didn't have many
friends left by that summer.

40:08.140 --> 40:13.176
I only really had cole
and his family.

40:14.478 --> 40:18.515
I felt like I had
to be so strong for them

40:18.517 --> 40:22.018
Because if they knew
what I was really thinking,

40:22.020 --> 40:25.021
They'd be terrified of me.

40:37.835 --> 40:39.135
Hey.

40:39.137 --> 40:42.972
Uh, you still
doing that catering job tonight?

40:42.974 --> 40:46.443
No, no. I'll bike over.

40:46.445 --> 40:48.978
Yeah, can I, uh,
can I borrow a dress?

40:48.980 --> 40:51.648
Mine are all dirty.

40:51.650 --> 40:54.117
Thanks.
Okay.

40:59.557 --> 41:03.126
[background chatter]

41:08.532 --> 41:11.534
[jazz music]

41:11.536 --> 41:19.542
♪

41:26.851 --> 41:29.219
Jesus, you're thin.
[both snicker]

41:29.221 --> 41:31.554
Do I look like a prostitute
in this?

41:31.556 --> 41:33.623
- I don't think
prostitutes wear black.

41:33.625 --> 41:36.025
- Oh, expensive ones do.

41:40.264 --> 41:42.632
Oh, terrific.

41:42.634 --> 41:45.869
- I thought he was cute.

41:45.871 --> 41:47.637
No?
[giggles]

42:30.648 --> 42:32.315
- Give me one of those.

42:34.885 --> 42:37.787
Let me ask you something.

42:37.789 --> 42:40.590
See that woman over there?

42:40.592 --> 42:43.059
Do you think she's attractive?

42:43.061 --> 42:45.562
- She's not my type.

42:47.164 --> 42:49.599
- [laughing]
I like you.

42:51.969 --> 42:54.637
Where do I know you from?

42:54.639 --> 42:57.106
- I'm a waitress
at the lobster roll. Perhaps--

42:57.108 --> 42:58.908
- Oh, my god.

42:58.910 --> 43:02.045
You're that poor little girl
who lost her baby, aren't you?

43:02.047 --> 43:06.349
I recognize you
from your picture in the paper.

43:06.351 --> 43:10.186
I wondered what happened to you
ever since I read that article.

43:12.189 --> 43:16.159
- Well, I'm still here.
- You taking care of yourself?

43:16.161 --> 43:19.095
- Trying.
- Good.

43:19.097 --> 43:23.299
You make sure you eat well,
exercise.

43:23.301 --> 43:26.302
If you need a valium,
let me know.

43:28.806 --> 43:31.074
See that fellow?

43:31.076 --> 43:33.910
The balding, squinty,
pretentious one?

43:33.912 --> 43:36.212
- Yes.

43:36.214 --> 43:40.350
- If I promised you a grand,
would you spill a drink on him?

43:59.003 --> 44:01.838
- Is that for me?
Thank you.

44:01.840 --> 44:04.941
- Excuse me, could you
get me a glass of water?

44:04.943 --> 44:08.044
Uh, and a very thin sliver
of cake, please. Thank you.

44:08.046 --> 44:09.312
- Sure.
- Oh, wait.

44:09.314 --> 44:11.714
Come here, dear.
Come here.

44:11.716 --> 44:14.017
Let me fix that for you.

44:14.019 --> 44:16.386
Hm.

44:16.388 --> 44:19.222
This couldn't be any tighter,
could it?

44:19.224 --> 44:22.191
There you go.
No ice in the water.

44:25.829 --> 44:27.897
- Want to have a look upstairs?

44:27.899 --> 44:29.232
- Uh, yeah.

44:29.234 --> 44:31.668
Yeah, I would love
to see upstairs.

44:31.670 --> 44:32.869
- Okay.

44:32.871 --> 44:35.004
[giggling]

44:35.006 --> 44:37.373
- Scotty?
- Oh, hey.

44:37.375 --> 44:38.975
- What are you doing here?

44:38.977 --> 44:40.276
- I came with ed.

44:40.278 --> 44:41.944
- You know him?
- Yeah, sure.

44:41.946 --> 44:42.979
We're old pals.
- Oh, my god.

44:42.981 --> 44:44.147
Can you get me his autograph?

44:44.149 --> 44:46.449
[both chuckling]

44:50.054 --> 44:53.289
- What's going on here?
- Nothing, dad.

44:55.993 --> 44:57.226
- Can I help you?

44:57.228 --> 44:59.095
- Oh, I was just looking
for the bathroom.

44:59.097 --> 45:02.165
- Oh, there's one on this level.

45:02.167 --> 45:04.233
Just, uh, past the kitchen.

45:04.235 --> 45:06.402
- Great. Thanks, man.

45:12.242 --> 45:14.444
- You want to get out of here?

45:17.414 --> 45:23.453
- Wow. I've never been
on one of these beaches.

45:23.455 --> 45:27.457
- You want to go in the water?
- No. Uh, I can't swim.

45:27.459 --> 45:30.026
- You live at the beach
and you can't swim?

45:30.028 --> 45:31.461
That's a travesty.

45:31.463 --> 45:33.196
- Not really.

45:33.198 --> 45:35.198
- Well, I'm a swimmer.
I'll teach you.

45:35.200 --> 45:37.333
- [chuckles]
right.

45:40.437 --> 45:43.506
- So it's nice to see you again.

45:43.508 --> 45:44.874
Alone.

45:46.477 --> 45:48.277
Clothed.

45:48.279 --> 45:53.049
- Yeah. Yeah.

45:53.051 --> 45:56.052
- You're married?
- I am.

45:56.054 --> 45:58.054
- You're not wearing a ring.

45:58.056 --> 46:01.491
- Well, I-I take it off
when I work.

46:01.493 --> 46:02.825
- Why?

46:02.827 --> 46:05.828
- Better tips.

46:05.830 --> 46:08.931
- So that guy in the driveway,
he's...He's your husband?

46:13.170 --> 46:16.305
I don't believe you.

46:16.307 --> 46:19.776
Married people
don't fuck like that.

46:19.778 --> 46:23.146
- Marriage means different
things to different people.

46:23.148 --> 46:26.983
- What does it mean to you?

46:26.985 --> 46:31.120
- Well, I-I used to think it
meant there was this one person

46:31.122 --> 46:34.190
I would put above anyone else.

46:34.192 --> 46:37.126
Above myself.

46:37.128 --> 46:40.797
- And now?

46:40.799 --> 46:43.833
- Now I just
hope I don't kill him.

47:00.450 --> 47:03.386
- I got married young.

47:03.388 --> 47:06.489
Straight out of college.

47:06.491 --> 47:08.357
I had a great girlfriend.
She was beautiful.

47:08.359 --> 47:10.993
She was rich.

47:10.995 --> 47:14.163
She was kind of artsy,

47:14.165 --> 47:15.932
And I wanted to be
beautiful, rich,

47:15.934 --> 47:18.601
And artsy, so I married her.

47:18.603 --> 47:21.070
And I loved her.
I should mention that.

47:21.072 --> 47:23.039
I did love her.

47:23.041 --> 47:26.242
- And now?

47:26.244 --> 47:27.944
- I still love her.

47:32.516 --> 47:36.018
But if I had to do it again I--

47:36.020 --> 47:39.188
I'd have waited just
a little bit longer...

47:39.190 --> 47:42.458
Given myself
a little more time to...

47:42.460 --> 47:44.861
To see who I might become.

47:53.337 --> 47:56.606
There's this hypothesis
in theoretical physics

47:56.608 --> 48:01.077
That I used to love back
at school, about time travel.

48:01.079 --> 48:03.913
About what would happen
if you could travel back in time

48:03.915 --> 48:09.886
And make a different choice
in your past,

48:09.888 --> 48:13.289
How that would affect your life
in the future.

48:13.291 --> 48:17.460
So the theory goes that, um,

48:17.462 --> 48:20.396
Your true life, your first life,

48:20.398 --> 48:23.399
Continues as is, unchanged,

48:23.401 --> 48:24.934
But at the moment of decision,

48:24.936 --> 48:30.039
A new life
splits off along a tangent

48:30.041 --> 48:32.441
Into a parallel universe.

48:37.114 --> 48:40.650
So you could, in a way...

48:40.652 --> 48:43.119
Live both lives.

48:56.533 --> 48:59.602
I've been thinking
about you all week.

49:03.640 --> 49:05.041
Have you been thinking about me?

49:05.043 --> 49:08.611
- Yes. Of course.

49:13.317 --> 49:16.986
- Well, what do you want
to do now?

49:16.988 --> 49:20.723
- I want you to kiss me,
but I don't think--

49:56.360 --> 49:59.328
So you're talking to everyone
who was there that night?

49:59.330 --> 50:00.997
- That's right.

50:03.200 --> 50:05.101
- The thing is, detective, I...

50:05.103 --> 50:08.604
I really doubt it was anyone
at the party that ran him down.

50:08.606 --> 50:10.106
- And what makes you say that?

50:10.108 --> 50:12.341
- Well, everyone
at the party was a local,

50:12.343 --> 50:14.610
But the road where he died,

50:14.612 --> 50:17.246
That leads to one
of those new fancy clubs

50:17.248 --> 50:18.781
That tourists like to go to.

50:18.783 --> 50:23.486
I don't know why anyone from the
party would be headed that way.

50:23.488 --> 50:25.654
- He was.

50:25.656 --> 50:28.758
- Yeah. I suppose that's true.

50:28.760 --> 50:32.028
- Where were you staying
that night?

50:32.030 --> 50:33.329
- I told you.

50:33.331 --> 50:35.564
- You drove back to the city.

50:35.566 --> 50:37.633
- Yeah. That's right.

50:37.635 --> 50:40.770
- So you think I'm barking
up the wrong tree?

50:40.772 --> 50:45.207
- I don't know. I just want to
help you do your job.

50:45.209 --> 50:47.076
I'll do anything to find out
what happened to him.

50:47.078 --> 50:52.715
I...I can't believe he's gone.

51:20.110 --> 51:22.244
[tires screeching]
- whoo-hoo!

51:37.160 --> 51:40.162
[edgy guitar music]

51:40.164 --> 51:46.335
♪

51:46.337 --> 51:48.537
- ♪ hello, mister

51:48.539 --> 51:51.740
♪ pleased to meet ya

51:51.742 --> 51:54.677
♪

51:54.679 --> 51:59.315
♪ I wanna hold her,
I wanna kiss her ♪

51:59.317 --> 52:03.486
♪

52:03.488 --> 52:05.588
♪ she smelled
of daisies ♪

52:05.590 --> 52:08.124
♪ she smelled of daisies
